            <h2><strong>Conservation Volunteer - Marataba National Park</strong></h2>
            <h4>June 2019 - July 2019</h4>
            <img style="vertical-align:top; height:240px; border-radius:150px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; width: auto;" src="~/img/Marataba.jpg" alt="Working with Kids in Kolkata, India" class="img-thumbnail">
            <br />
            <p>
                <i>Marataba is a 21,000 hectare, privately managed section of the Marakele National Park in Limpopo, South Africa</i>
                <br /><br />
                I spent three weeks living and working on Marataba National Park to conserve the bushveld and protect the endangered species inhabited there. I was involved in laborious activities such as bush clearing and rebuilding perimeter fences as well
                as tracking and relocating animals such as kudu and buffalo.

            </p>
